nformula_104\nwhich is the eikonal equation and it holds for all formula_105, formula_106, formula_107, since the variable formula_61 is absent. Other laws of optics like Snell's law and Fresnel formulae can be similarly obtained by considering discontinuities in formula_84 and formula_85.\nGeneral equation using four-vector notation.\nIn four-vector notation used in special relativity, the wave equation can be written as\nformula_111\nand the substitution formula_112 leads to\nformula_113\nTherefore, the eikonal equation is given by\nformula_114\nOnce eikonal is found by solving the above equation, the wave four-vector can be found from\nformula_115"}
