{"id": "731824", "revid": "27823944", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=731824", "title": "March to Fuzz", "text": "March to Fuzz is a compilation album by American rock band Mudhoney, released in January 2000 by Sub Pop Records. Disc 1 is a collection of the band's most popular songs, such as \"Here Comes Sickness\" and \"Sweet Young Thing Ain't Sweet No More.\" Disc 2 is a collection of rare tracks, b-sides such as \"Butterfly Stroke,\" and covers such as \"The Money Will Roll Right In.\"\nThe booklet that comes with the digipak album features an introduction by Sup Pop co-founder Bruce Pavitt, \"Corporate Associate.\" The remainder of the booklet includes comments by band members Mark Arm and Steve Turner about each of the 52 songs.\nTrack listing.\nAll tracks written by Mudhoney unless otherwise noted.\nDisc 1 - Best Of\nDisc 2 - Rarities"}
